  <text>
    <front>
      <div type="summary">
        <p>
          The Manager of the publishing company The Hogarths Press suggests a number of the pocket edition of Vita Sackville-West's novel The Edwardians to be put for sale at the
          Birmingham Repertory Theatre, as the latter was producing a play based on the novel.
        </p>
      </div>
    </front>
    <body>
      <div type="letter">
        <opener>
          <dateline>
            <placeName></placeName>
            <date when="1934-09-06">September 6th.1934</date>
          </dateline>
          <address>
            <addrLine>The Manager,</addrLine>
            <addrLine><orgName key="Q4916786">Birmingham Repertory Theatre,</orgName></addrLine>
            <addrLine>Birmingham.</addrLine>
          </address>
          <salute>
            Dear Sir,
          </salute>
        </opener>
        <p>
          <persName key="Q235505">Miss Sackville-West</persName>'s <title type="novel"><emph rend="underlined">Edwardians</emph></title> is, I believe, to<lb/>
          be produced at the <orgName>Birmingham Repertory Theatre</orgName> on Saturday<lb/>
          the 15th <choice><abbr>inst.</abbr><expan>instante mense</expan></choice> We publish a pocket edition of the novel at<lb/>
          <choice><abbr>3&#x2F;6d</abbr><expan>three and six</expan></choice>
                    <note>
                      <p>I have decided to treat '3&#x2F;6d' as one unit of abbreviation and not only expand the 'd' for 'danarius', as the term '3&#x2F;6d' was
                        commonly used to signify a value less than a pound, i.e. three shillings and sixpence.
                       </p>
                     </note>, and I am writing to ask whether you would consider<lb/>
          taking a certain number for sale at the theatre. We could<lb/>
          supply them at a discount of 33 &#8531;&#x25;, and should be glad to pay<lb/>
          carriage.
        </p>
        <closer>
          <salute>
            Yours faithfully,
          </salute>
          <signed>
            <orgName key="Q1623362">THe Hogarth Press,</orgName><lb/>
            Manager
          </signed>
          <seg>

          </seg>
        </closer>
      </div>
    </body>
